    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "Join Trashlab — the operating system for waste haulers.\n\nhttps://trashlab.com/\n\nWe unify dispatch, billing, calls and routes into one powerful platform that transforms how waste fleets operate.\n\nBy combining real‑time vehicle tracking, route optimization, integrated billing, and customer communications, Trashlab helps haulers cut costs, speed up collections, and deliver exceptional service. If you’re passionate about building scalable software that drives operational efficiency and sustainability in the waste industry, come help us build the future of waste operations.\n\nWe’re hiring a Senior Product Engineer to help us build core product from the ground up. This is a high-ownership, full-stack role for someone who cares deeply about product, moves quickly, and wants to work on software that customers depend on every day.\n\nYou’ll work closely with founders, talk to users, and ship across the stack. The problems are real, the workflows are messy, and the opportunity to build meaningful software is huge.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\n - Own and ship product across dispatch, billing, routing, and support\n\n - Build full-stack systems that are simple for customers and robust under the hood\n\n - Turn operational pain points into well-designed product solutions\n\n - Help shape product direction through strong engineering and customer judgment\n\n - Use AI tools where they create leverage for the team and product\n\nWhat we’re looking for\n\n - Strong product instinct\n\n - Proven full-stack engineering ability\n\n - High ownership and comfort with ambiguity\n\n - Strong communication in a remote team\n\n - Interest in operationally complex software and pragmatic use of AI\n\nHow we work\n\n - Remote-first, hiring across LATAM\n\n - Small team, fast execution, high trust\n\n - Founders still in the code and close to product\n\n - TypeScript, React, Node.js, Postgres, Expo / React Native, Mapbox\n\nIf you want high scope, high ownership, and the chance to help build a category-defining product in an overlooked industry, this role is for you.\n\nInterview Process\n\n - Silver Screening interview\n\n - Take home challenge\n\n - Client resume review + take home review\n\n - Client technical interview",
